<h1>WestWind Reference Project</h1>

<p>
    This sample project demonstrates the expected architecture for the group project.
    The application uses a layered design with a Business Logic Layer (BLL),
    Data Access Layer (DAL), and Blazor UI.
</p>

<hr />

<h3>Architecture Overview</h3>

<ul>
    <li><b>UI (Blazor Components)</b> – Displays data and calls services</li>
    <li><b>BLL (Services)</b> – Contains business rules and validation</li>
    <li><b>DAL (DbContext)</b> – Provides database access through EF Core</li>
</ul>

<h3>Architecture Rules</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Blazor components must call BLL services for all data operations.</li>
    <li>Blazor components must NOT access DbContext directly.</li>
    <li>Each BLL method creates its own DbContext using IDbContextFactory.</li>
    <li>All validation and business rules belong in the BLL.</li>
    <li>UI components display messages but do not enforce business rules.</li>
    <li>CRUD services follow the pattern: Guard → Context → Query → Action → Save.</li>
    <li>Read-only queries should use AsNoTracking().</li>
    <li>Friendly error messages should be surfaced from the BLL to the UI.</li>
</ol>

